info.headline: Flood Advisory issued June 19 at 10:00AM EDT until June 19 at 1:00PM EDT by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: ...FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CDT/1 PM EDT/ TODAY... * WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected. * WHERE...Portions of Big Bend Florida and Panhandle Florida, including the following counties, in Big Bend Florida, Liberty. In Panhandle Florida, Bay, Calhoun, Gulf and Washington. * WHEN...Until noon CDT /100 PM EDT/. * IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 900 AM CDT /1000 AM EDT/, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. Minor flooding is ongoing or expected to begin shortly in the advisory area. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Lynn Haven, Blountstown, Orange, Bristol, Ebro, Youngstown, Saunders, Nixon, Cairo, Fountain, Broad Branch, Singer Road, Bennett, Majette, Gainer Spring, Camp Flowers, Kinard, Moose Pond, Bayou George and Frink. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
